    "instruction": "From the metric.csv aggregates (use the full-series thresholds already computed in memory), select only (cmdb_id, kpi_name) series where global_p95 > global_p05 (i.e., non-constant series). Then, using metric rows restricted to the incident window Mar 21, 2022 07:00:00 to 07:30:00 UTC+8, for each selected series compute: total_points_in_window, count_high_breach (value >= global_p95), earliest_high_breach_timestamp (or null), count_low_breach (value <= global_p05), earliest_low_breach_timestamp (or null), window_max, window_min, global_p95, global_p05. Also compute a simple severity score per series = max( if count_high_breach>0 then (window_max - global_p95)/max(1e-9,global_p95) else 0, if count_low_breach>0 then (global_p05 - window_min)/max(1e-9,global_p05) else 0 ). Return the top 20 series sorted by descending severity score (ties broken by descending max(count_high_breach,count_low_breach), then by total_points_in_window). Limit output to the described columns and at most 20 rows. If no non-constant series have breaches in the window, explicitly report that fact."
}

